# Swift Code Style

## Language Best Practices
- **Prefer structs over classes** unless reference semantics are explicitly required
- **Prefer value types** over reference types for thread safety
- **Avoid force unwrapping (`!`)** — use `guard let` or `if let` to handle optionals safely; force-unwrap only when absolutely certain and justified with a comment
- **Avoid blocking the main thread** — network calls, DB operations, and heavy computations must run on background threads

## Naming Conventions (Swift API Design Guidelines)
| Scope | Convention |
|---|---|
| Properties & functions | `camelCase` |
| Types (structs, classes, enums, protocols) | `PascalCase` |
| JSON keys | `snake_case` |

Function names must be expressive and clear.

## Async / Concurrency
- Avoid nested completion handlers
- Use **Combine** or **structured concurrency (`async/await`)** for all async operations
- Publish UI-facing state on the **main actor** — use `receive(on: DispatchQueue.main)` before mutating `@Published` properties, or annotate with `@MainActor` where appropriate
- Avoid blocking the main thread in `View.body` or `onAppear`

## SOLID & Error Handling
- Follow **SOLID principles** in all modifications
- Implement proper error handling — never swallow errors silently

## Comments & Documentation
- Preserve all existing documentation comments
- Write clear inline comments for non-obvious logic

## Formatting
Use idiomatic Swift formatting and keep builds warning-free. Follow SwiftLint or SwiftFormat only if the project later adds configuration for them.

## Project-Specific File Conventions
| Purpose | File |
|---|---|
| SwiftUI screens | `ImageSummarization/Views` |
| UI state and user-flow orchestration | `ImageSummarization/ViewModels` |
| OCR, ML, validation, summarization, nutrition lookup | `ImageSummarization/Services` |
| Lightweight value types and Codable/API contracts | `ImageSummarization/Models` |
| Wrappers and shared helpers | `ImageSummarization/Utilities` |
| ML models and model documentation | `ImageSummarization/Resources/MLModels` |
| Project generation / build settings | `project.yml` |
| Secrets / credentials | Keychain, build configuration, or platform-approved secure storage — never committed plaintext |
